Caption:
🥶 AC Buying Guide 💯

👉🏻 Best ACs on Our Broadcast Channel

Non-Inverter AC:

Non-inverter AC turns off the compressor after reaching the target temperature and turns it back on when the temperature rises.

Ideal for large spaces like big rooms, shops, or offices.

Works well in rooms that get a lot of sunlight or where windows/doors are opened frequently.

Great for areas with frequent power cuts. Perfect for this summer if you’re in a place where people come and go often.

Inverter AC:

The compressor runs continuously at a low power level.

Best for rooms that are airtight and don’t receive much sunlight.

Saves electricity by maintaining a steady temperature without frequent on/off cycles.

Cools efficiently and uses less power compared to non-inverter ACs.
